messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hi, I need someone at 15012 Spring Street. Union Grove. I need an ambulance.
Okay, ma'am. What do you need the ambulance for?
I have a boy that was underwater and he's not breathing.
How old is the boy?
Uh, four.
How long was he in the water?
We don't know, like a couple of minutes.
Was he in a pool or...?
Yeah, swimming pool.
Okay, do you want to do CPR?
I'm sorry, I can't hear you.
Do you want to do CPR, ma'am?
Um, they're trying right now. Can you talk someone through it?
Yep, if you want to put someone on the phone with me.
Okay, Scott, she's going to talk us through CPR.
Hello?
Hi, is he responding at all?
No, there's no pulse.
I'm pushing. I'm doing chest compressions.
Okay, you need to make sure his mouth and airway are not blocked.
Okay.
I need you to put one hand on his forehead and the fingers of your other hand under the bony part of his chin and gently tilt the head back. Just a little.
Okay.
Do you see him breathing at all?
No, he's still not breathing.
Okay, I need you to give two breaths, one second each. Make sure the chest rises.
Okay. Come on, come on.
His sister is crying in the background.
I understand, but I need you to stay focused. Is he breathing now?
No, there's still no pulse.
Okay, keep doing chest compressions. Push hard and fast, about 2 inches deep and 100-120 compressions per minute.
Okay, I'm doing it.
Wait, I think he's moving.
Do you feel him breathing? Is there a pulse?
Yes, I think I feel a pulse. He's breathing!
Great, roll him onto his side and keep his airway open. Continue to monitor him closely.
Okay, we're doing that. Is the ambulance coming?
Yes, they are on their way. How is his skin color?
Kind of hard to see, but he looks okay. He's breathing.
Is the deputy there yet?
Yes, he's here.
Okay, I'm going to keep you on the line until the ambulance arrives.
That's fine. Thank you.
You're doing great. They should be there any second.
I hear the sirens. They're coming.
Good. Just stay calm, help is almost there.
Thank you so much for your help.
You're welcome. You're doing a great job.
They are here now.
Okay, I'm going to let you go now. Thank you for your help. Goodbye.
Goodbye.
